{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891324912,"sessionID":"ses_284a3f022ffepV3qnah8C7bRgF","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5f1f8c001g45AxeSbWEQa1l","messageID":"msg_d7b5e0d9a001iBkXNVZOfUMTo7","sessionID":"ses_284a3f022ffepV3qnah8C7bRgF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-211bff22bbc24fdd87aa583e168b8f3b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: Go Unit Tests for pkg/workloadmanager\n\n## Overview\n\nThis proposal outlines a comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module to improve code quality, reliability, and maintainability of the AgentCube workload management system.\n\n**AR:** AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe workloadmanager module is a critical component responsible for managing sandbox lifecycles, Kubernetes resource reconciliation, and garbage collection. Currently, test coverage is partial and concentrated in some submodules (gc, handler, api, config) while the core reconciliation logic lacks comprehensive unit tests.\n\nThis testing initiative aims to:\n\n1. **Ensure correctness** of reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **Validate error handling** paths and edge cases\n3. **Test condition management** and status updates\n4. **Cover finalizer management** for resource cleanup\n5. **Verify predicate logic** for event filtering\n6. **Provide regression protection** for future changes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope Components\n\nThe proposal focuses on the most critical and currently untested components:\n\n1. **Controller Reconciler** (`controller/reconciler/`):\n   - `codeinterpreter.go` - Core reconciliation logic (primary focus)\n   - `status.go` - Condition management utilities\n   - `finalizers.go` - Finalizer management\n   - `predicates.go` - Event filtering predicates\n   - `errors.go` - Error handling\n   - `controller.go` - Controller setup functions\n\n2. **Handler Extensions** (`handler/`):\n   - `sandbox.go` - SandboxHandler with deletion logic (supplementary)\n\n3. **Server Setup** (`server/`):\n   - `server.go` - Server initialization (supplementary)\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Integration tests with real Kubernetes clusters (separate effort)\n- End-to-end API tests (covered by existing handler tests)\n- Performance/load testing\n- Modules with existing adequate test coverage (gc, handler, api, config)\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Testing Framework\n\n- **Primary:** `testing` package (standard library)\n- **Assertions:** `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` and `require`\n- **Mocking:** `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock` for controller-runtime interfaces\n- **Kubernetes Testing:** `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for realistic scenario testing\n- **Fake Clients:** `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake` for mock Kubernetes API interactions\n\n### Test Categories\n\n#### 1. Unit Tests (Primary Focus)\n- Isolated function-level testing\n- Mock all external dependencies\n- Fast execution (< 1s per test)\n- High coverage of code paths\n\n#### 2. Reconciler Tests (Critical)\n- Full reconciliation cycle testing\n- Status condition updates\n- Error handling and retry logic\n- Finalizer lifecycle\n\n#### 3. Integration-Style Tests\n- Use fake client but test real logic\n- Test interaction between reconciler components\n- Verify Kubernetes resource creation/updates\n\n### Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage | Priority |\n|-----------|----------------|----------|\n| `codeinterpreter.go` | 85%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n| `status.go` | 90%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n| `finalizers.go` | 90%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n| `predicates.go` | 95%+ | P1 (High) |\n| `errors.go` | 80%+ | P1 (High) |\n| `controller.go` | 70%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n| `sandbox.go` | 75%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n| `server.go` | 70%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n\n## Detailed Test Plans\n\n### 1. CodeInterpreter Reconciler Tests (`codeinterpreter_reconciler_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Reconcile Method\n- [ ] Successful reconciliation of new CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] Reconciliation with existing sandbox (no changes)\n- [ ] Reconciliation with sandbox spec changes (update)\n- [ ] Reconciliation when sandbox not ready (requeue)\n- [ ] Reconciliation of deleted CodeInterpreter (cleanup)\n- [ ] Handling of missing CodeInterpreter (not found)\n- [ ] Adding finalizer on first reconciliation\n- [ ] Validation failure handling (invalid spec)\n- [ ] Sandbox creation failure handling\n- [ ] Sandbox update failure handling\n- [ ] Status update failure handling\n- [ ] Conflict error handling (retry logic)\n- [ ] ObservedGeneration tracking\n\n#### Reconcile Delete Method\n- [ ] Successful sandbox deletion\n- [ ] Handling missing sandbox (not found)\n- [ ] Sandbox deletion failure\n- [ ] Finalizer removal\n- [ ] Finalizer removal failure\n- [ ] Event recording for deletion\n\n#### Reconcile Sandbox Method\n- [ ] Create sandbox when not exists\n- [ ] Update sandbox when exists and spec changed\n- [ ] No update when spec unchanged\n- [ ] Skip update when pod being deleted\n- [ ] Error handling for Get failures\n\n#### Build Pod Spec Method\n- [ ] Build pod spec with custom image\n- [ ] Use default image when not specified\n- [ ] Include environment variables\n- [ ] Include resource limits\n- [ ] Handle nil resources\n\n#### Validate Spec Method\n- [ ] Valid spec passes\n- [ ] Empty image fails\n- [ ] Invalid resource spec handling\n\n#### Is Ready Method\n- [ ] Return true when pod ready\n- [ ] Return false when pod not ready\n- [ ] Return false when pod not found\n- [ ] Return false when pod being deleted\n\n#### Helper Functions\n- [ ] GetSandboxName generates correct name\n- [ ] convertEnvVars handles empty/nil env\n- [ ] convertResources handles limits/requests\n- [ ] podSpecsEqual comparison logic\n\n### 2. Status Management Tests (`status_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Set Condition\n- [ ] Add new condition to empty slice\n- [ ] Update existing condition with different status\n- [ ] Update existing condition with same status (update time only)\n- [ ] Update existing condition with different reason/message\n- [ ] Handle nil conditions pointer\n\n#### Get Condition\n- [ ] Find existing condition by type\n- [ ] Return nil for non-existent condition\n- [ ] Handle empty conditions slice\n\n#### Condition Checkers\n- [ ] IsReady returns true when Ready=True\n- [ ] IsReady returns false when Ready=False/missing\n- [ ] IsAvailable returns true when Available=True\n- [ ] IsProgressing returns true when Progressing=True\n- [ ] HasError returns true when Error=True\n\n#### Condition Setters\n- [ ] SetReadyCondition sets correct status\n- [ ] SetErrorCondition includes error message\n- [ ] ClearErrorCondition removes error condition\n- [ ] SetProgressingCondition sets correct status\n- [ ] SetAvailableCondition sets correct status\n- [ ] SetSandboxCreatedCondition sets correct status\n\n#### Condition Utilities\n- [ ] GetConditionMessage returns message or empty string\n- [ ] GetConditionReason returns reason or empty string\n\n### 3. Finalizers Tests (`finalizers_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Add Finalizer\n- [ ] Add finalizer to object without finalizers\n- [ ] Add finalizer when already exists (no-op)\n- [ ] Add multiple finalizers\n- [ ] Patch failure handling\n\n#### Remove Finalizer\n- [ ] Remove finalizer from object\n- [ ] No-op when finalizer not present\n- [ ] Remove finalizer from middle of list\n- [ ] Remove last finalizer\n- [ ] Patch failure handling\n\n#### Has Finalizer\n- [ ] Return true when finalizer present\n- [ ] Return false when finalizer absent\n- [ ] Handle empty finalizers slice\n\n#### Owner References\n- [ ] GetOwnerReference returns UID when found\n- [ ] GetOwnerReference returns not found when missing\n- [ ] Match by APIVersion and Kind\n\n### 4. Predicates Tests (`predicates_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n- [ ] Update returns true when generation changes\n- [ ] Update returns false when generation same\n- [ ] Update returns false when nil objects\n- [ ] Create returns true\n- [ ] Delete returns true\n\n#### LabelChangedPredicate\n- [ ] Update returns true when labels differ\n- [ ] Update returns true when label count differs\n- [ ] Update returns false when labels same\n- [ ] Handle nil label maps\n\n#### AnnotationChangedPredicate\n- [ ] Update returns true when annotations differ\n- [ ] Update returns true when annotation count differs\n- [ ] Update returns false when annotations same\n- [ ] Handle nil annotation maps\n\n#### PauseAnnotationPredicate\n- [ ] Update returns false when paused annotation present\n- [ ] Update returns true when paused annotation absent\n- [ ] Update returns false when paused=false\n- [ ] Create returns true when not paused\n- [ ] Delete returns true\n\n#### Utility Functions\n- [ ] IsBeingDeleted returns true with deletion timestamp\n- [ ] HasOwnerReference returns true when UID matches\n- [ ] AddOwnerReference adds controller reference\n- [ ] AddLabels merges new labels with existing\n- [ ] AddAnnotations merges new annotations with existing\n- [ ] IsPodReady returns true when PodReady condition true\n- [ ] GetPodCondition finds specific condition\n\n### 5. Error Handling Tests (`errors_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### ReconcilerError\n- [ ] Error() formats message without wrapped error\n- [ ] Error() formats message with wrapped error\n- [ ] Unwrap() returns wrapped error\n- [ ] Retryable flag preserved\n\n#### Error Constructors\n- [ ] NewReconcilerError creates error with all fields\n- [ ] NewValidationFailedError creates non-retryable error\n- [ ] NewSandboxCreateFailedError creates retryable error\n- [ ] NewSandboxUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n- [ ] NewSandboxDeleteFailedError creates retryable error\n- [ ] NewStatusUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n- [ ] NewFinalizerFailedError creates retryable error\n\n### 6. Controller Setup Tests (`controller_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Controller Config\n- [ ] DefaultControllerConfig returns sensible defaults\n- [ ] All expected fields populated\n\n#### Controller Manager\n- [ ] NewControllerManager creates manager successfully\n- [ ] Manager configured with correct options\n- [ ] Error handling for manager creation failure\n\n#### Setup Functions\n- [ ] SetupWithManager sets up both reconcilers\n- [ ] setupAgentRuntimeReconciler configures controller\n- [ ] setupCodeInterpreterReconciler configures controller\n- [ ] Error handling for setup failures\n\n#### Utilities\n- [ ] GetSandboxName generates correct format\n- [ ] SandboxResult struct initialization\n\n### 7. Sandbox Handler Tests (`sandbox_handler_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Handle Delete Sandbox\n- [ ] Successfully delete sandbox with valid session ID\n- [ ] Return error when session ID empty\n- [ ] Return 404 when session not found\n- [ ] Handle SandboxClaim deletion\n- [ ] Handle Sandbox deletion\n- [ ] Return 500 for store errors\n- [ ] Handle K8s delete failures\n- [ ] Cleanup store even when K8s delete fails\n- [ ] Handle not found from K8s (already deleted)\n\n### 8. Server Tests (`server_test.go`)\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n\n#### Server Initialization\n- [ ] NewServer creates server with correct configuration\n- [ ] Server registers expected routes\n- [ ] Server uses correct middleware\n- [ ] Server health endpoint returns 200\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Reconciler (Week 1-2)\n1. Implement `status_test.go` (foundation for other tests)\n2. Implement `finalizers_test.go`\n3. Implement `errors_test.go`\n4. Setup test utilities and helpers\n\n### Phase 2: CodeInterpreter Reconciler (Week 2-3)\n1. Implement `codeinterpreter_reconciler_test.go`\n2. Focus on main reconciliation logic\n3. Cover success and error paths\n\n### Phase 3: Predicates and Utilities (Week 3)\n1. Implement `predicates_test.go`\n2. Implement `controller_test.go`\n3. Add any missing utility tests\n\n### Phase 4: Handler and Server (Week 4)\n1. Implement `sandbox_handler_test.go`\n2. Implement `server_test.go`\n3. Review and fill gaps\n\n### Phase 5: Validation and Coverage (Week 4)\n1. Run full test suite\n2. Verify coverage targets\n3. Add missing edge case tests\n4. Documentation and cleanup\n\n## Testing Utilities\n\nTo support the test suite, we'll create shared utilities:\n\n```go\n// testutil/reconciler_test.go\npackage testutil\n\n// Helper functions for creating test objects\nfunc NewTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\nfunc NewTestPod(name, namespace string) *corev1.Pod\nfunc NewFakeClient() client.Client\n\n// Helpers for assertions\nfunc AssertConditionEqual(t *testing.T, conditions []metav1.Condition, expectedType, expectedStatus string)\nfunc AssertHasFinalizer(t *testing.T, obj client.Object, finalizer string)\n```\n\n## CI/CD Integration\n\n### Pre-commit Checks\n- Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` on every commit\n- Fail if coverage drops below threshold (70% overall, 80% for new code)\n\n### Pipeline Requirements\n- All tests must pass before merge\n- Generate coverage reports and upload to coverage service\n- Run tests on PR creation and update\n\n### Coverage Enforcement\n- Set minimum coverage thresholds in CI\n- Block merges that reduce coverage\n- Generate coverage badges for README\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Benefits\n1. **Improved Reliability**: Catch bugs early in development cycle\n2. **Faster Development**: Refactor with confidence using test safety net\n3. **Better Documentation**: Tests serve as executable documentation\n4. **Reduced Debugging Time**: Quick failure identification\n5. **Regression Prevention**: Ensure existing functionality works after changes\n\n### Risks\n1. **Time Investment**: Initial test writing requires significant effort\n2. **Maintenance Overhead**: Tests need updates when code changes\n3. **False Confidence**: Tests only cover what they test; gaps may exist\n4. **Test Brittleness**: Over-specific tests may break with unrelated changes\n\n### Mitigation Strategies\n1. Start with critical paths and expand iteratively\n2. Focus on behavior testing over implementation details\n3. Use table-driven tests for comprehensive coverage\n4. Regular test maintenance and refactoring\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Integration Tests Only\n- **Pros**: Tests real system behavior\n- **Cons**: Slower, harder to isolate failures, complex setup\n- **Verdict**: Complementary, not replacement for unit tests\n\n### Alternative 2: Property-Based Testing\n- **Pros**: Finds edge cases unit tests miss\n- **Cons**: Steeper learning curve, more complex setup\n- **Verdict**: Consider for future enhancement\n\n### Alternative 3: Minimal Testing (Current State)\n- **Pros**: No upfront investment\n- **Cons**: High bug risk, slower development, technical debt\n- **Verdict**: Unsustainable for critical path code\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required Packages\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` (already in go.mod)\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` (already in go.mod)\n- `k8s.io/client-go` (already in go.mod)\n\n### Test Data\n- Use existing CRD definitions from `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- Mock client-go and controller-runtime interfaces\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. All proposed test files implemented and passing\n2. Overall test coverage for `pkg/workloadmanager` ≥ 80%\n3. Critical components (`codeinterpreter.go`, `status.go`, `finalizers.go`) ≥ 85% coverage\n4. All tests run in < 30 seconds total\n5. No flaky tests (100% pass rate over 100 runs)\n6. Tests integrated into CI/CD pipeline\n7. Code review approval from 2 reviewers\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should we use `envtest` for more realistic integration-style tests?\n2. What should be the minimum coverage threshold enforced in CI?\n3. Should we add benchmark tests for performance-critical paths?\n\n## Timeline\n\n| Week | Milestone |\n|------|-----------|\n| 1 | Phase 1: Core utilities (status, finalizers, errors) |\n| 2 | Phase 1 complete, start Phase 2 (reconciler) |\n| 3 | Phase 2 complete, start Phase 3 (predicates) |\n| 4 | Phase 3 & 4 complete, Phase 5 (validation) |\n| 5 | Code review, refinements, final documentation |\n\nTotal estimated effort: **5 weeks** (1 developer)\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [client-go library](../deployment/client-go.md) - Kubernetes client interfaces\n- [workloadmanager design](./design.md) - Module architecture\n- [GC design](./design-gc.md) - Garbage collector design\n\n## References\n\n- [Go Testing Best Practices](https://go.dev/doc/tutorial/add-a-test)\n- [Kubernetes Controller Runtime Testing](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/testing.html)\n- [Testify Documentation](https://github.com/stretchr/testify)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [63:7] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [106:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [173:2] declared and not used: logger\nERROR [242:5] undefined: podSpecsEqual\nERROR [267:29] undefined: convertEnvVars\nERROR [274:25] undefined: convertResources\nERROR [326:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go\">\nERROR [57:3] unknown field MetricsBindAddress in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [58:3] unknown field Port in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [62:3] unknown field SyncPeriod in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [88:17] undefined: AgentRuntimeReconciler\nERROR [98:15] cannot use ctrl.Options{…} (value of struct type controllerruntime.Options) as \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller\".TypedOptions[reconcile.Request] value in argument to ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).WithEventFilter(&ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate{}).WithOptions\nERROR [98:28] unknown field MaxConcurrentReconciles in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [118:15] cannot use ctrl.Options{…} (value of struct type controllerruntime.Options) as \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller\".TypedOptions[reconcile.Request] value in argument to ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}).WithEventFilter(&ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate{}).WithOptions\nERROR [118:28] unknown field MaxConcurrentReconciles in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go\">\nERROR [50:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go\">\nERROR [94:36] m.storeClient.GetSandbox undefined (type store.Store has no field or method GetSandbox)\nERROR [189:34] m.storeClient.ListSandboxes undefined (type store.Store has no field or method ListSandboxes)\nERROR [239:55] too many arguments in call to m.storeClient.StoreSandbox\n\thave (context.Context, string, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\n\twant (context.Context, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli