{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891333276,"sessionID":"ses_284a3f022ffepV3qnah8C7bRgF","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5f4078001Z6PuwFIa3TkWBn","messageID":"msg_d7b5f2027001bp3lFKCJqv4Uqx","sessionID":"ses_284a3f022ffepV3qnah8C7bRgF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-68e6007d7b1646f4971fd932b445c2f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Go Unit Tests for pkg/workloadmanager\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This proposal outlines a comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module to improve code quality, reliability, and maintainability of the AgentCube workload management system.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n8: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n9: **Language:** Go\n10: **Size:** L\n11: \n12: ## Purpose\n13: \n14: The workloadmanager module is a critical component responsible for managing sandbox lifecycles, Kubernetes resource reconciliation, and garbage collection. Currently, test coverage is partial and concentrated in some submodules (gc, handler, api, config) while the core reconciliation logic lacks comprehensive unit tests.\n15: \n16: This testing initiative aims to:\n17: \n18: 1. **Ensure correctness** of reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n19: 2. **Validate error handling** paths and edge cases\n20: 3. **Test condition management** and status updates\n21: 4. **Cover finalizer management** for resource cleanup\n22: 5. **Verify predicate logic** for event filtering\n23: 6. **Provide regression protection** for future changes\n24: \n25: ## Scope\n26: \n27: ### In-Scope Components\n28: \n29: The proposal focuses on the most critical and currently untested components:\n30: \n31: 1. **Controller Reconciler** (`controller/reconciler/`):\n32:    - `codeinterpreter.go` - Core reconciliation logic (primary focus)\n33:    - `status.go` - Condition management utilities\n34:    - `finalizers.go` - Finalizer management\n35:    - `predicates.go` - Event filtering predicates\n36:    - `errors.go` - Error handling\n37:    - `controller.go` - Controller setup functions\n38: \n39: 2. **Handler Extensions** (`handler/`):\n40:    - `sandbox.go` - SandboxHandler with deletion logic (supplementary)\n41: \n42: 3. **Server Setup** (`server/`):\n43:    - `server.go` - Server initialization (supplementary)\n44: \n45: ### Out-of-Scope\n46: \n47: - Integration tests with real Kubernetes clusters (separate effort)\n48: - End-to-end API tests (covered by existing handler tests)\n49: - Performance/load testing\n50: - Modules with existing adequate test coverage (gc, handler, api, config)\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 472. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Go Unit Tests for pkg/workloadmanager\n\n## Overview\n\nThis proposal outlines a comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module to improve code quality, reliability, and maintainability of the AgentCube workload management system.\n\n**AR:** AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe workloadmanager module is a critical component responsible for managing sandbox lifecycles, Kubernetes resource reconciliation, and garbage collection. Currently, test coverage is partial and concentrated in some submodules (gc, handler, api, config) while the core reconciliation logic lacks comprehensive unit tests.\n\nThis testing initiative aims to:\n\n1. **Ensure correctness** of reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **Validate error handling** paths and edge cases\n3. **Test condition management** and status updates","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775891333267,"end":1775891333274}}}}
